          "type": "content_block",
          "settings": {
            "label": "How it began",
            "heading": "Fourteen years in the air. One idea on the ground.",
            "text": "<p>Our founder spent over a decade on international aviation routes — Tokyo, London, New York, Dubai. Every layover was an education. In every city, there were well-engineered personal electronics that simply didn't exist in Indian retail, or arrived through grey markets at double the price with no accountability.</p><p>He came home to Bengaluru in early 2024 with a notebook full of products and a single question: why should access to quality be a function of geography?</p>",
            "quote": "I spent years handing out noise-cancelling headphones to business-class passengers and thinking — why can't my mother find something half as good in a shop in Bengaluru? That gap became Blissway."
          }
        },
